  "prompt": "Where can I get an explainer video for $100?",
  "response": "Here are some platforms where you might find an explainer video for around $100:\n\n1. Fiverr\n- Many freelancers offer basic explainer video services\n- Prices range from $50-$200\n- Wide variety of styles and quality\n\n2. Freelancer.com\n- Competitive bidding platform\n- Multiple video creators with different pricing\n- Can find budget-friendly options\n\n3. Upwork\n- Freelance marketplace with video creators\n- Filter by price and portfolio\n- Can negotiate rates\n\n4. Canva\n- DIY video creation tool\n- Low-cost templates\n- Can create simple explainer videos yourself\n\n5. VideoScribe\n- Animation software\n- Affordable whiteboard-style explainer videos\n- Monthly subscription options\n\nTips:\n- Expect basic, shorter videos at this price point\n- Quality may vary\n- Check portfolios and reviews\n- Be clear about your requirements\n- Consider complexity of your project\n\nRecommendations:\n- Start with Fiverr for affordable options\n- Check multiple platforms\n- Request samples\n- Have a clear script ready\n\nKeep in mind that professional, high-quality explainer videos typically cost $500-$2,000.",
